Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_sequential(25.10)                              report_sequential(25.10)

Name
       report_sequential - Reports information about sequentials the design

Syntax
       report_sequential

       [-help]

       [-deleted]

       [-full]

       [-hinst <hInst_names>]

       [-mapped]

       [-optimized]

       [-out_file <string>]

       Reports  information  about sequentials the design. Sequentials are the
       elements that have a library is_sequential tag.  These  can  be  flops,
       latches, and clock gates.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each report_sequential parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_sequential

       -deleted
              Generates a report with the deleted flops and the reason.

       -full  Generates a report with the sequential name, whether it was  in-
              ferred  or instantiated, the type of sequential, and the type of
              reset.

       -hinst <hInst_names>
              Hinst for the report. By default, the design is reported.

       -mapped
              Generates a report with synthesis requirements modified  to  map
              the sequential.

       -optimized
              Generates  a  report  with sequentials optimized to constants or
              are unloaded, but have not been removed.

       -out_file <file_name>
              File to dump the report. Default is stdout

Examples
              * The following command reports the deleted flops:

       innovus 1> report_sequential -deleted

       Sequential elements: deleted flops

       -------------------------------------

          Reason      Instance Name

       -------------------------------------

       unloaded       foo/bar/q_reg[15]

       unloaded       foo/bar/q_reg[31]

       unloaded       foo/bar/q_reg[47]

       unloaded       foo/bar/q_reg[63]

       unloaded       foo/bar/q_reg[79]

       constant 0     moo/ff_reg_9

              * The following command reports the optimized flops:

                innovus 2> report_sequential -optimized

                Sequential elements: optimized flops

                ------------------------------------------

                  Reason      Instance Name

                ------------------------------------------

                constant 0     RESULTS_CONV_INST/out_p1_reg[7]

                constant 0     TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/alu_cmd_reg[3]

                constant 0     TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/read_data_reg

                constant 0     TDSP_CORE_INST/EXECUTE_INST/read_port_reg

